Colombian Stock Movers: Rubiales, Petrominerales, Ecopetrol

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-22T20:56:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/colombian-stock-movers-rubiales-petrominerales-ecopetrol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 3.3 percent to 13,187 while the Colcap
Index declined 2.9 percent to 1,607.91.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based company that
explores for and produces oil in Colombia, fell the most since
it began trading in Bogota last month. The company said in a
filing that it didn’t find oil in at least three exploration
wells and has yet to fully resume production after protests.
Shares fell 11 percent to 48,200 pesos.  Oil companies dropped as crude fell to a six-week low after
the  Federal Reserve  cited “significant downside risks” to the
economy of the U.S., the world’s biggest crude consuming nation.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  South America , fell 7.1 percent
to 1,300 pesos, the lowest since it began trading in July 2010.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell 4.4 percent, the most since November, to 3,865 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, fell 5 percent,
the most in a month, to 43,700 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
